I got it to work by doing this:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Download Installer in AppStore</li>
  <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT201372">Copy High Sierra Installer to bootable USB drive</a></li>
  <li>Boot from USB drive</li>
  <li>Install High Sierra</li>
</ol>

<p>This installes a working macOS High Sierra, but doesnâ€™t have APFS enable on the SSD.
To convert the SSD into APFS, follow those steps:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Boot from USB drive Again</li>
  <li>Run Disk Utility, select <em>Macintosh HD</em></li>
  <li>Go to <em>Edit &gt; Convert to APFSâ€¦</em></li>
  <li>Reboot</li>
</ol>

<p>If macOS doesnâ€™t boot, install High Sierra again on the APFS filesystem.</p>

